Eli Brandt (ebrandt@jarthur.cs.hmc.edu) wrote:
: Raw white noise samples are all that comes to mind.  But this approach
: to ciphertext detection is easily foiled by adding some redundancy to
: the ciphertext, so that it no longer appears random.  

Sure.  From crypto lore, a typical method is to slice a file in half and
send the second half first, thus burying the incipit.  Nevertheless,
categorizing files still must be done to narrow the search space.  At
least I think so.
